Create a  HelloController.fs  file inside the  Hello  folder.  The  index  function tell us what the html will be but we still need to tell Saturn to return it as an html page. We also need to tell Saturn what where the page is  Insert the following into the file.  namespace Hello

open Saturn
open Giraffe.ResponseWriters

module Controller =
    let indexAction =
        htmlView (Views.index)

    let helloView = scope {
        get "/" indexAction
    }  The  indexAction  tell Saturn to create an html page using the  index  function inside "HelloViews.fs"  helloView  let Saturn know that the page is located at the root.

Computation expression used to combine  HttpHandlers  in declarative manner.  The result of the computation expression is a standard Giraffe  HttpHandler which means that it's easily composable with other parts of the Giraffe ecosystem.  Example:  let headerPipe = pipeline {
    set_header "myCustomHeader" "abcd"
    set_header "myCustomHeader2" "zxcv"
}

let endpointPipe = pipeline {
    plug fetchSession
    plug head
    plug requestId
}

Computation expression used to creating routing and combining  HttpHandlers ,  pipelines  and  controllers  together.  Result of the computation expression is standard Giraffe's  HttpHandler which means that it's easily composable with other parts of the ecosytem.  Example:  let topRouter = scope {
    pipe_through headerPipe
    not_found_handler (text "404")

    get "/" helloWorld
    get "/a" helloWorld2
    getf "/name/%s" helloWorldName
    getf "/name/%s/%i" helloWorldNameAge

    //scopes can be defined inline to simulate `subRoute` combinator
    forward "/other" (scope {
        pipe_through otherHeaderPipe
        not_found_handler (text "Other 404")

        get "/" otherHelloWorld
        get "/a" otherHelloWorld2
    })

    // or can be defined separatly and used as HttpHandler
    forward "/api" apiRouter

    // same with controllers
    forward "/users" userController
}

Defines top-level router used for the application. It's calling  IApplicationBuilder.UseGiraffe  Input:   HttpHandler  application {
    ...
    router myRouter
}

Adds pipeline to the list of pipelines that will be used for every request  Input:   HttpHandler  application {
    ...
    pipe_through requestId
}

Adds global error handler for exceptions not handled anywhere else. It's using  IApplicationBuilder.UseGiraffeErrorHandler  Input:   Exception -> ILogger -> HttpHandler  application {
    ...
    error_handler (fun e log -> text e.Message)
}

Defines URL on which application will be hosted. Should include port.  Input:   string  application {
    ...
    url "http://0.0.0.0:8085/"
}

Enables in-memory session cache. Required if you used  fetchSession  plug.  application {
    ...
    memory_cache
}

Enables automatic gzip compression  application {
    ...
    use_gzip
}

Enables using static file hosting. Input path defines  WebRoot  and  ContentRoot  of application  Input:   string  application {
    ...
    use_static "static"
}

Defines configuration that can be used with  HttpContext.GetConfiguration ()  function. Configuration function is evaluated once, during first request of the application.  Input:   unit -> 'a  application {
    ...
    use_config (fun _ -> "config")
}

Redirect all HTTP request to HTTPS  application {
    ...
    force_ssl
}

Enables application level CORS protection. First parameter is name of the policy. Second parameter is configuration builder setting policy options.  Input:   string -> (CorsPolicyBuilder -> unit)  application {
    ...
    use_cors "CORS_policy" (fun builder -> ())
}

Enables IIS integration  application {
    ...
    use_iis
}

Enables default JWT authentication. First parameter is private key used to signing. Second one defines issuer of the token.  Input:   string -> string  application {
    ...
    use_jwt_authentication "mySecretKey" "lambdafactory.io"
}

Enables JWT authentication with custom configuration  Input:   JwtBearerOptions -> unit  application {
    ...
    use_jwt_authentication_with_config (fun opts -> ())
}

Enables default cookies authentication  Input:   string  application {
    ...
    use_cookies_authentication "lambdafactory.io"
}

Enables cookies authentication with custom configuration  Input:   CookieAuthenticationOptions -> unit  application {
    ...
    use_cookies_authentication_with_config (fun opts -> ())
}

Enables default GitHub OAuth authentication  Input:   string -> string -> string  application {
    ...
    use_github_oauth "myClientId" "myClientSecret" "/login"
}

Enables GitHub OAuth authentication with custom configuration  Input:   OAuthOptions -> unit  application {
    ...
    use_github_oauth (fun opts -> ())
}

Enables custom OAuth authentication  Input:   string -> (OAuthOptions -> unit)  application {
    ...
    use_custom_oauth "LinkedIn" (fun opts -> ())
}    Functions below enables you to add any configuration with using standard ASP.NET builders
